										<h3 class="pb-5 text-black font-black text-3xl"><a href="https://abilityoptions.org.au/ability-options-is-a-ttp-provider/" title="Ability Options is a TTP Provider">Ability Options is a TTP Provider</a></h3>
										<p class="pb-5 text-black font-medium text-lg">From 1 July 2019, providers of attendant care and community and centre-based activities have access to a higher support price limit through a Temporary Transformation Payment (TTP). The TTP assists providers with any costs associated in transitioning to the NDIS. &nbsp; Ability Options is a registered TTP Provider. &nbsp; The NDIA have increased existing service [&hellip;]</p>
										<a href="https://abilityoptions.org.au/ability-options-is-a-ttp-provider/" class="uppercase inline-block text-black font-black text-lg border-b-2 border-green"> Read more </a>
									</div>
								</div>
